The paper deals with natural language processing and recurrent neural networks, which are commonly studied in the computer science sub-category of Computational Linguistics (cs.CL). The paper also discusses a modified LSTM model, which falls under the sub-category of Machine Learning (cs.LG) and Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI). The benchmarks conducted in the paper involve tasks such as sentiment analysis and news article classification, which are related to Computer Vision (cs.CV) and Information Retrieval (cs.IR) respectively. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.CL, followed by cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.CV, and cs.IR.
